    {
      "number": 3,
      "title": "正在 — Indicating an Ongoing Action",
      "explanation": "正在 (zhèng zài) is used to indicate an action that is currently in progress. Structure: Subject + 正在 + Verb (+ 呢). It is similar to the English present continuous tense. 呢 can be added at the end for emphasis. 在 alone can also be used: 我在吃饭 = I am eating.",
      "examples": [
        {
          "chinese": "他正在和同事见面。",
          "pinyin": "Tā zhèng zài hé tóng shì jiàn miàn.",
          "english": "He is currently meeting with his colleague."
        },
        {
          "chinese": "我正在介绍新同事呢。",
          "pinyin": "Wǒ zhèng zài jiè shào xīn tóng shì ne.",
          "english": "I'm in the middle of introducing the new colleague."
        }
      ],
